title: Any one going for the T206 Chase Trophy PSA 7
author: tcdyess

posts.post_title: Any one going for the T206 Chase Trophy PSA 7
posts.post_content:
I might jump into the fray...  2 hours left and at 1k.  Pop of 2 highest graded, don't want to jack it up for anyone here who is intent on not losing it...

Tim

I thought about jumping in, but it got a little steep right at the end.

I did win the other probstein auction for the Joss 7. Which I think was a freaking steal.
yes what a steal on the joss!!

[quote name="lharri3600" post=991685]yes what a steal on the joss!![/QUOTE]

Thanks, definitely one of the best values I've had this year. Hope it's not an indicator the 206 market is weakening though... Didn't imagine getting a Joss 7 for $1k anytime soon.

No worries, t206 market isn't going anywhere but up.  I actually paid over $600 a piece for 3 sgc 84 commons with probstein in the same auction....granted, they are low pop. Cards, but that's alot of money for sgc graded t206s.....

[quote name="CMIZ5290" post=991744]No worries, t206 market isn't going anywhere but up.  I actually paid over $600 a piece for 3 sgc 84 commons with probstein in the same auction....granted, they are low pop. Cards, but that's alot of money for sgc graded t206s.....[/QUOTE]

Funny, I was watching all 3 of them... If the Joss went over my max bid I was going to turn around and go for those 3... A little interesting though how much less of a premium the Joss went for, if you think about it, I only paid 400 more for it than the commons. That gap for high graded commons and high graded mid tier HOFs is narrowing, or, I got an exceptional deal. 

Either way, stoked to have the Joss.

That was a really high quality Probstein sale though

hopefully, we'll have some more high grade in soon, we'll bring them to the national , booth #153
